<p>
  I'm a veterinarian and software developer currently living in Northern
  Virginia. I graduated from veterinary school in 2017 and practiced full time
  as a small animal vet for 5-6 years before changing careers. Currently, I work
  as a software developer and occasionally work at as a veterinarian on
  weekends.
</p>
<h3>About This Site</h3>
<p>
  This website is written in the Go programming language using mostly the
  standard library and a few small dependencies. It's self-hosted on a little
  <a href="https://www.raspberrypi.com/">Raspberry Pi</a>
  that sits on my desk. It mainly consists of a simple http server, html
  templates using Go's built in templating library, and a little bit of css and
  js. Comments are stored in a postgres database, which is probably overkill.
  The source code is viewable on my github at
  <a href="https://github.com/RyanNicoletti/ryannicoletti.net">
    github.com/RyanNicoletti/ryannicoletti.net
  </a>
  .
</p>
<h3>Indie Web</h3>
<p>
  The
  <a href="https://indieweb.org/">indie web</a>
  consists of websites created, owned, and maintained by individuals. It's a
  niche alternative idea to what most people know as the modern web. One of the
  main principles of the indie web community, is having ownership over your own
  domain, website, and data. I've always been a fan of the "web 1.0", before it
  was over taken by a few large social media and advertising companies and was
  more just a place to share information.
  <br />
  <br />
  This website is my small contribution to the indie web. I use it to share
  things I write about and projects I'm working on, as well as to share other
  websites I find interesting.
</p>
